  heroImageAlt="Dolphin DMB-004 manual-clean disc stack centrifuge system"
  category="products"
  categoryLabel="Dolphin Basket Centrifuges"
  toc={[
    { id: "ai-summary", label: "AI Summary" },
    { id: "specifications", label: "DMB-004 Specifications" },
    { id: "capacity-by-application", label: "Capacity by Application" },
    { id: "manual-vs-self-cleaning", label: "Manual-Clean vs. Self-Cleaning" },
    { id: "key-applications", label: "Key Applications" },
    { id: "faq", label: "Frequently Asked Questions" },
  ]}
  relatedApplications={[
    { label: "Waste Oil Centrifuge", href: "/waste-oil-centrifuge/" },
    { label: "Fuel Oil Centrifuge", href: "/fuel-oil-centrifuge/" },
    { label: "Lube Oil Centrifuge", href: "/lube-oil-centrifuge/" },
  ]}
  relatedProducts={[
    { label: "DMB-007 Manual-Clean Centrifuge", href: "/centrifuges/dmb-007/" },
    { label: "DMB-013 Manual-Clean Centrifuge", href: "/centrifuges/dmb-013/" },
    { label: "DMPX-010 Self-Cleaning Centrifuge", href: "/centrifuges/dmpx-010/" },
  ]}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article class="prose-dolphin max-w-none">

    <div id="ai-summary" class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-6 not-prose mb-8">
      <p class="text-base italic text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>AI Summary:</strong> Dolphin Centrifuge supplies the DMB-004 — a manual-clean disc stack centrifuge clarifier rated at 4 GPM on diesel (13 cSt) and 8,600 RPM with a 1 HP motor. The most economical entry point in the DMB manual-clean range, ideal for small turbine lube oil purification, diesel polishing, and hydraulic oil maintenance in low-volume applications. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of experience in centrifugal separation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="specifications">DMB-004 Specifications</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Parameter</th>
            <th>Value</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Separation type</td><td>Two-phase clarifier (liquid-liquid or liquid-solid)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Diesel throughput</td><td>~4 GPM (13 cSt at operating temperature)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Rated throughput (water)</td><td>~6 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bowl speed</td><td>8,600 RPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Drive motor</td><td>1 HP</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cleaning method</td><td>Manual (bowl disassembly required for solids removal)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bowl construction</td><td>Carbon steel standard</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Power supply</td><td>115V or 230V single-phase / 60 Hz (other voltages available)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">Throughput figures are for typical fluids at listed conditions. Actual capacity varies with feed viscosity, temperature, density difference, and solids loading.</p>

    <h2 id="capacity-by-application">DMB-004 Capacity by Application (GPM)</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Application / Fluid</th>
            <th>Throughput (GPM)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Gas oil at 40&deg;C</td><td>~5 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Diesel fuel (13 cSt)</td><td>~4 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lube oil (R&amp;O)</td><td>~2 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lube oil (detergent)</td><td>~2 GPM</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Steam turbine oil</td><td>~4 GPM</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 id="manual-vs-self-cleaning">Manual-Clean vs. Self-Cleaning: Choosing the Right Approach</h2>
    <p>
      The DMB-004 is a manual-clean clarifier: accumulated solids are retained in the bowl until the machine is stopped, the bowl disassembled, and the solids manually removed. This requires periodic planned cleaning shutdowns — typically every few days to weeks depending on the solids loading of the feed.
    </p>
    <p>
      For applications with low solids content — clean <a href="/diesel-centrifuge/">diesel polishing</a>, turbine <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/">lube oil</a> with minimal particulate — manual cleaning is infrequent and the DMB-004 delivers excellent value. The simpler design means lower initial cost, lower operating complexity, and straightforward maintenance.
    </p>
    <p>
      If your feed has significant solids loading, or if uninterrupted 24/7 operation is critical, consider Dolphin's self-cleaning <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-010/">DMPX-010</a> instead. The DMPX-010 ejects solids automatically without stopping and operates continuously without cleaning shutdowns.
    </p>

    <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
    <div class="not-prose my-10 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold bg-gold/10 p-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="text-navy font-bold text-lg mb-1">Need help selecting between DMB-004 and DMPX-010?</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Our applications engineers will evaluate your solids loading, throughput, and uptime requirements to recommend the right model — at no charge.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="shrink-0 inline-block bg-gold text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gold/90 transition-colors text-center">
        Request a Quote &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 id="key-applications">Key Applications</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10 not-prose">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Small Turbine Lube Oil Systems</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Steam turbines and gas turbines up to ~1,000 HP with lube oil reservoirs of 300–1,000 gallons. The DMB-004 purifies lube oil in a continuous bypass loop at 2–4 GPM, removing water and wear particles to extend oil life and protect bearings.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Diesel Fuel Polishing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Generator sets, small standby power systems, and diesel storage tanks requiring continuous fuel polishing at ~4 GPM. The DMB-004 removes free water and particulates from diesel in a compact package suited for space-constrained generator rooms.</p>
        <a href="/diesel-centrifuge/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-navy hover:text-gold transition-colors">Diesel Centrifuge Details &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Hydraulic Oil Purification</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Small hydraulic systems on CNC equipment, presses, and industrial machinery. The DMB-004 removes water ingress and fine particulates from hydraulic circuits in a bypass loop at 2 GPM, maintaining oil cleanliness and preventing valve and actuator wear.</p>
        <a href="/hydraulic-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-navy hover:text-gold transition-colors">Hydraulic Oil Centrifuge Details &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Low-Volume Industrial Oil Polishing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Quench oil, heat treatment oil, metalworking oil, and similar industrial fluids requiring periodic polishing to remove water and solids accumulation. The DMB-004 handles these low-throughput applications cost-effectively where <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">self-cleaning operation</a> is not required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the throughput of the DMB-004?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMB-004 processes ~4 GPM of diesel, ~5 GPM of gas oil at 40&deg;C, ~2 GPM of lube oil (R&amp;O), and ~4 GPM of steam turbine oil. Rated at 6 GPM on water-viscosity fluid.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the difference between DMB-004 and DMPX-010?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMB-004 is manual-clean — solids accumulate until the bowl is manually disassembled and cleaned. The <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-010/">DMPX-010</a> is self-cleaning with automatic solids ejection. The DMB-004 costs less and is appropriate for low-solids feeds; the DMPX-010 is better for continuous operation with moderate to high solids.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What applications is the DMB-004 best suited for?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Small turbine <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/">lube oil systems</a> (up to ~1,000 HP), diesel polishing on small generators, hydraulic oil purification, and low-volume oil polishing where solids content is low and periodic cleaning is acceptable.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">How often does the DMB-004 bowl need to be cleaned?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Cleaning frequency depends on your feed fluid's solids content. For clean turbine lube oil or polished diesel, intervals can range from several weeks to months. For higher-solids feeds, weekly cleaning may be required. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> to estimate cleaning intervals for your application.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What voltages are available for the DMB-004?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Standard configurations are 115V or 230V single-phase / 60 Hz. Other voltages and frequencies are available for international installations. The <a href="/centrifuges/dmb-007/">DMB-007</a> and larger DMB models typically use 460V / 3-phase. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact Dolphin Centrifuge</a> to confirm the right electrical configuration for your site.
      </p>
    </details>

    <h2>Related Resources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/centrifuges/dmb-007/">DMB-007 Manual-Clean Centrifuge (~7 GPM)</a></li>
      <li><a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-010/">DMPX-010 Self-Cleaning Centrifuge (~7 GPM)</a></li>
      <li><a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">Disc Stack Centrifuge Overview</a></li>
      <li><a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/">Lube Oil Centrifuge Applications</a></li>
      <li><a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact Us for DMB-004 Pricing</a></li>
    </ul>

  </article>

  <!-- Bottom CTA Bar -->
  <div class="not-prose mt-12 rounded-xl bg-navy px-8 py-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-6">
    <div class="flex-1">
      <p class="text-white font-bold text-xl mb-1">Ready to order the DMB-004?</p>
